<P><A id=3Dcost name=3Dcost></A><A id=3Dwgt name=3Dwgt></A>Scrolls are =
listed above by=20
increasing price, then alphabetically. The COST field denotes the base =
price of=20
each item. WGT specifies the weight (100 zorkmids weighs 1).</P>
<P><A id=3Dprob name=3Dprob></A>Scrolls comprise 16% of all =
randomly-generated items=20
in the main dungeon, 18% in containers, 22% on the Rogue level, and 1% =
in hell.=20
PROB is the relative probability of each subtype. Scrolls appear 1/8 =
cursed, 3/4=20
uncursed, and 1/8 blessed.</P>
<P>Scrolls of mail exist only if this ability was compiled into your =
copy of the=20
game, and if you have the "mail" option enabled. When new email arrives =
(or=20
every 1999+d(3000) turns if playing on an Amiga or DOS platform), the =
"mail=20
daemon" will deliver a scroll of mail. All of these scrolls are =
considered=20
uncursed, and they cannot be changed into another object in any way.</P>
<P><A id=3Dmrkr name=3Dmrkr></A>MRKR specifies the value used to =
determine the=20
number of magic marker charges needed to write a scroll of that type, or =
zero if=20
it cannot be written. The actual number of charges used will be a random =
amount=20
from MRKR/2 to MRKR-1; if your marker has fewer than MRKR/2 charges, you =
will be=20
unable to attempt to write the scroll.</P>
<P>Wizards have a base 1/3 chance of writing an unknown scroll, and all =
other=20
classes have a base 1/15 chance; your chance generally improves with =
higher=20
luck, to a maximum of about 98% for Wizards and 32% for other classes. =
You can=20
only write scrolls on blank paper, which can be made by getting any =
scroll wet=20
(except mail) or cancelling any scroll (except mail). Failure to write =
the=20
scroll will cause the blank scroll to be used up. You can select =
non-blank=20
scrolls to write on, but this will abuse your wisdom and you will be =
told, "That=20
scroll is not blank!"</P>
